{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/variantref\/refsink()"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"refSink"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariantRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" on a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"text":" with a floating reference","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will convert the floating reference into a full reference.  Calling","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_ref_sink()"},{"text":" on a non-floating ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"text":" results in an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"additional normal reference being added.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In other words, if the "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is floating, then this call “assumes","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ownership” of the floating reference, converting it to a normal","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reference.  If the ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is not floating, then this call adds a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"new normal reference increasing the reference count by one.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All calls that result in a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"type":"text","text":" instance being inserted into a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"container will call ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_variant_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on the instance.  This means"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that if the value was just created (and has only its floating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference) then the container will assume sole ownership of the value"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"at that point and the caller will not need to unreference it.  This","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"makes certain common styles of programming much easier while still"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"maintaining normal refcounting semantics in situations where values","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"are not floating.","type":"text"}]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/refSink()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/VariantProtocol-Implementations"]]},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:4GLib15VariantProtocolPAAE7refSinkAA0B3RefVSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib10VariantRefV","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"refSink"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariantRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"refSink()","symbolKind":"method"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"identifier